		"name": "TaskManager",
		"description": "TaskManager API provides secure authentication and task management features.\n\nThis collection includes APIs for:\n\n- User Registration and Login using JWT authentication\n    \n- Creating, retrieving, updating, and deleting tasks\n    \n- Secure access to protected routes using Bearer tokens\n    \n\nJWT tokens are automatically generated on login and stored in Postman environment variables for seamless testing.\n\nTech Stack:\n\n- Node.js\n    \n- Express.js\n    \n- MongoDB\n    \n- JWT Authentication\n    \n\nSteps to use:\n\n1. Import the collection into Postman\n    \n2. Set base_url in environment (e.g. [http://localhost:9000](http://localhost:5000))\n    \n3. Register a user\n    \n4. Login to generate JWT token\n    \n5. Test all protected task APIs",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
